<%# 2026-05-18 (live cover refresh) — Bundle modal composite wrapper
    partial. Single render target for two surfaces:

      1. Initial render through `app/views/bundles/games_pane.html.erb`
         when the user opens the bundles modal — the games_pane Turbo
         Frame body renders this partial above the all-games table.
      2. Turbo Stream `replace` from `BundleCoverBuild` after a
         membership change rebuilds the composite — the job
         broadcasts a `<turbo-stream action="replace">` targeting
         `bundle_modal_composite_<id>` and pointing at this same
         partial so the live-updated composite (or, on the empty-
         bundle path, the netflix-3 placeholder) lands inside the
         same wrapper without closing + reopening the modal.

    The dom_id wrapper is rendered UNCONDITIONALLY (both populated
    and empty paths share the same target id) so the first add to a
    previously-empty bundle still hits a stable target — without
    that, the Turbo Stream replace would have nothing to swap.

    Locals:
      bundle — the Bundle record. Drives the populated / empty
               branch + cell map + cell anchors.
%>
<div id="bundle_modal_composite_<%= bundle.id %>">
  <% if bundle.games.any? %>
    <%# CSS-positioned composite cover grid is now owned by
        `Bundle::ModalCompositeComponent`. The component pulls
        `bundle.games.first(9)` and renders each cell over a 3:4 canvas
        using `Composite::CellMap.for(n)` — the same source of truth
        the libvips JPEG builder uses. %>
    <%= render Bundle::ModalCompositeComponent.new(bundle: bundle) %>
  <% else %>
    <%# Empty-bundle placeholder. Mirrors the populated composite
        slot above: same `width: 100%` + `aspect-ratio: 3 / 4` outer
        box. Reuses the shelf-tile netflix-3 grid markup so the
        visual reads as "bundle waiting for members" rather than
        empty whitespace above the [+] add row. %>
    <%= render Bundle::EmptyCoverPlaceholderComponent.new(bundle: bundle, modifier: :modal) %>
  <% end %>
</div>
